<p>Launching an online store in 2026 has never been more accessible, but choosing the right e-commerce platform is critical to your success. The best e-commerce website builders handle everything from product listings and payment processing to shipping calculations and inventory management, letting you focus on growing your business instead of fighting with technology.</p>

<p>Our <a href="/">website builder comparison page</a> provides a comprehensive overview of all the leading platforms, including their e-commerce capabilities and pricing.</p>

<h2>What to Look for in an E-commerce Builder</h2>

<p>Before diving into specific platforms, here are the essential features every e-commerce builder should provide.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Payment processing:</strong> Support for major payment gateways including credit cards, PayPal, Apple Pay, and Google Pay</li>
  <li><strong>Product management:</strong> Easy tools for adding products, variants, images, descriptions, and pricing</li>
  <li><strong>Inventory tracking:</strong> Automatic stock level monitoring with low-stock alerts</li>
  <li><strong>Shipping tools:</strong> Real-time shipping rate calculations and label printing</li>
  <li><strong>Tax handling:</strong> Automatic tax calculations based on customer location</li>
  <li><strong>Mobile commerce:</strong> A shopping experience optimized for phone and tablet users</li>
  <li><strong>Security:</strong> SSL certificates and PCI compliance to protect customer data</li>
</ul>

<h2>Top E-commerce Website Builders</h2>

<h3>Shopify: Best Overall for E-commerce</h3>

<p>Shopify dominates the e-commerce space for good reason. The platform powers over 4 million online stores worldwide and provides the most comprehensive set of selling tools available. From a single dashboard, you can manage products, process orders, track inventory across multiple locations, and sell on social media channels and marketplaces like Amazon and eBay.</p>

<p>Shopify Payments eliminates the need for third-party payment processors and offers competitive processing rates. The platform's app store includes thousands of e-commerce extensions for everything from product reviews and loyalty programs to dropshipping and print-on-demand fulfillment. For a detailed comparison with another popular builder, see our <a href="/blog/shopify-vs-wix-comparison">Shopify vs Wix breakdown</a>.</p>

<h3>Wix eCommerce: Best for Small Product Catalogs</h3>

<p>Wix has grown into a capable e-commerce platform for sellers with smaller product catalogs. The visual editor makes it easy to create beautiful product pages, and the built-in tools cover the essentials including payment processing, inventory management, discount codes, and abandoned cart recovery. Wix is an excellent choice if you sell fewer than 100 products and want maximum design flexibility.</p>

<h3>Squarespace Commerce: Best for Visual Brands</h3>

<p>Squarespace's award-winning design templates make it the go-to choice for brands where visual presentation is paramount. Fashion labels, artisans, photographers selling prints, and food businesses benefit from Squarespace's stunning product galleries and clean checkout experience. The Commerce plans include inventory management, customer accounts, and product variants.</p>

<h3>BigCommerce: Best for Scaling Businesses</h3>

<p>BigCommerce targets growing businesses that need enterprise-level features without enterprise-level complexity. The platform includes built-in multi-channel selling, unlimited product variants, advanced SEO tools, and no transaction fees on any plan. BigCommerce is the strongest choice for businesses that anticipate rapid growth and need a platform that can scale with them.</p>

<h2>E-commerce Pricing Breakdown</h2>

<p>E-commerce plans cost more than standard website plans due to the additional functionality. Here is what you can expect to pay monthly for each platform's entry-level e-commerce plan.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Shopify Basic:</strong> $39/month with Shopify Payments included</li>
  <li><strong>Wix Business:</strong> $27/month with online payment acceptance</li>
  <li><strong>Squarespace Commerce Basic:</strong> $33/month with 3% transaction fee</li>
  <li><strong>BigCommerce Standard:</strong> $39/month with no transaction fees</li>
</ul>

<p>Remember to account for payment processing fees, which typically run 2.5-3% plus a fixed per-transaction charge regardless of the platform. See our <a href="/blog/website-builder-pricing-guide">pricing guide</a> for a complete cost analysis.</p>

<h2>Essential Features for Online Store Success</h2>

<h3>Abandoned Cart Recovery</h3>

<p>Studies show that nearly 70% of online shopping carts are abandoned before checkout. Abandoned cart recovery emails automatically remind customers about items they left behind and can recover 5-15% of lost sales. Shopify and Wix include this feature in their e-commerce plans, while Squarespace reserves it for higher tiers.</p>

<h3>Multi-Channel Selling</h3>

<p>Selling only through your website limits your reach. The best e-commerce platforms let you sync your product catalog with Facebook Shops, Instagram Shopping, Amazon, eBay, and even in-person point-of-sale systems. Shopify and BigCommerce lead in multi-channel capabilities.</p>

<h3>Mobile Shopping Experience</h3>

<p>With mobile commerce accounting for over 70% of e-commerce traffic, your store must deliver a flawless mobile shopping experience. Look for builders that offer <a href="/blog/mobile-responsive-website-builders">mobile-responsive themes</a>, fast loading speeds on mobile networks, and mobile-optimized checkout flows.</p>

<h2>Tips for Launching Your Online Store</h2>

<p>Once you have chosen your platform, follow these steps to set yourself up for success.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Invest in product photography:</strong> High-quality images are the single biggest factor in online purchase decisions</li>
  <li><strong>Write detailed product descriptions:</strong> Include dimensions, materials, care instructions, and unique selling points</li>
  <li><strong>Set up SEO from day one:</strong> Optimize product titles, descriptions, and images for search engines using our <a href="/blog/website-builder-seo-guide">SEO guide</a></li>
  <li><strong>Configure shipping clearly:</strong> Be transparent about shipping costs and delivery times to reduce cart abandonment</li>
  <li><strong>Test the checkout process:</strong> Place a test order yourself to experience what your customers will see</li>
</ul>

